We've seen so many people saying the power scales are broken but what if they aren't trying to kill broly. They are having to suppress their own powers while trying to not get killed.  They find another saiyan who is being forces to fight against his own will. No way would goku resort to killing him. It's a complete redo of broly. Still the badass fighter just gone berserk as kale did but under the control of a saiyan seeking revenge. Broly would make for an awesome addition to the z fighters in a new arc as well.

text: *Storyline should be* :  • *Saiyan babies with potential* are sent off to planets to either die or become exceptional - power wise. Few get selected. Considered an honor.  • Bardock being one of Planet Vegeta's elite soldiers, had his son arranged to conquer Earth, Kakarot having a weak power level, was sent purely on *potential* , in hopes that one day he would be formidable like Bardock.  • *Prince Vegeta having a high power level* as an infant, was seen as a symbol of pride for the king and assurance for the future.  • King Vegeta's pride took a blow when a baby named *Broly* , surpassed even the king's son - would later realize he's the *strongest infant to be recorded* , ever.  • King Vegeta, envisioned this baby would outdo his son, *overshadow* him and would rule with power.  • *King Vegeta had Broly sent to a brutal planet to die* . Deceiving Broly's father, who thought his son was sent on an honorable conquest to grow formidable.  • Fast forward to the present and guess who's still *alive* .  • Broly's father having found out where his son was cast off to, would find himself aware of the King's betrayal and went in search of Broly.   • Broly was found as the *last* survivor on the planet.  • Lastly, Broly's father guides him, aims *revenge* against the mighty Bardock's son, Kakarot and the Prince Vegeta himself.
author: Randy Marsh

text: Piccolo's appearance in this movie was so unexpected to me. And I am so confused about where does this franchise want to go with Piccolo. I mean in this movie we had only the most popular characters like Goku, Vegeta and Frieza from the Z-Fighters. There weren't even characters like Gohan or Android 17. So for Piccolo to be given screentime among such top tier characters, even if it's very little, really shocks me. No doubt Piccolo until Android saga was arguably the second strongest Z-Fighter second only to Goku even in terms of popularity he was among the top characters of Dragon Ball franchise but ever since then he has been falling and falling. But then they suddenly tease us of giving him the same glory he once used to have by placing him in Universe-6 arc and now giving us a glimpse of him in this movie. But then again, you never know what's going on in their minds regarding Piccolo.
